Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 05-31-18.   
Count 1 - OWI (5th) - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four and one-half (4 1/2) years consecutive to Case File 14 CF 545.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through; 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacist unless otherwise approved; 
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is entitled to 115 days credit.    
Minutes.

Defendant in custody.
Defendant waives his right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 1 for trial.
ARRAIGNMENT - 
Information filed.  Copy served on defense counsel.
GUILTY plea entered to count 1, OWI - 5th offense.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, OAR.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) pay $600.00 fine plus costs, total of $1,769.00;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
4) AODA assessment and follow through/ Intoxicated Driver assessment;
5) Spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to begin immediately upon completion of the 12 month condition time on count 3 of 14 CF 545;
6) Obtain GED or HSED.
In addition, the Court orders a twenty-four (24) month period of DL revocation and IID.
Minutes.
